A '''Bottlebrush''' is a [[cave]] formation which results when a [[stalactite]] is immersed in rising water which is [[supersaturation|supersaturated]] with [[calcium carbonate]].  The stalactite becomes coated with [[Spar (mineralogy)|pool spar]].<ref>[http://www.goodearthgraphics.com/virtcave/bottlebr/bottlebr.html Bunnell, Dave, ''The Virtual Cave: Bottlebrushes'']</ref>

