'''Jansha''' is an [[impact crater]] on the southern hemisphere of [[Saturn]]'s moon [[Enceladus (moon)|Enceladus]].  Jansha was first observed in ''[[Cassini-Huygens Mission|Cassini]]'' images during that mission's March 2005 flyby of Enceladus.  It is located at 30.4° South [[Latitude]], 156.9° West [[Longitude]], and is 9.8 kilometers across.<ref name=gpn />  Several of the southwest-northeast trending fractures that are prevalent in the region cut across Jansha, forming canyons several hundred meters deep along Jansha's rim.

Jansha is named after the hero in "The Tale of Jansha" (or Janshah) from ''[[The Book of One Thousand and One Nights]]''.

