'''Mucrocetin''' is a [[snake venom]] platelet-agglutinating factor,<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Huang KF, Ko TP, Hung CC, Chu J, Wang AH, Chiou SH | title = Crystal structure of a platelet-agglutinating factor isolated from the venom of Taiwan habu (Trimeresurus mucrosquamatus) | journal = The Biochemical Journal | volume = 378 | issue = Pt 2 | pages = 399–407 | date = March 2004 | pmid = 14613481 | doi = 10.1042/BJ20031507 | pmc = 1223962 }}</ref> that acts in a [[Von Willebrand factor|vWF]]-independent manner. Binds specifically to platelet [[GP1BA|GPIbalpha (GP1BA)]] to a distinct binding site from that of flavocetin-A.

The platelet-agglutinating factor isolated from the venom of Taiwan habu ([[Protobothrops mucrosquamatus]]).

